<h1>Problem 1227 - 2019 IMOSL, C2</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>You are given a set of \(n\) blocks, each weighing at least \(1\); their total weight is \(2n\). Prove that for every real number \(r\) with \(0 \leq r \leq 2n-2\) you can choose a subset of the blocks whose total weight is at least \(r\) but at most \(r+2\).</p>
